      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 360: The congestion callback fires on every RTCP check while `pondLoss` remains above 3%, with no hysteresis or recovery signal. Video has a 4s cooldown, but audio RTCP also runs every 4s, so sustained loss can force repeated multiplicative reductions until video reaches minimum bitrate even if the first reduction was enough. Add hysteresis/state in audio, or send explicit congestion enter/recover events so video only reacts once per congestion episode. ```suggestion\nif (pondLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD \u0026\u0026 !audioCongested_) {\n    audioCongested_ \u003d true;\n    cb(pondLoss);\n} else if (pondLoss \u003c AUDIO_CONGESTION_RECOVERY_THRESHOLD) {\n    audioCongested_ \u003d false;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "3b3c7421f96e69829f1a7e7278b1778a57af330e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
